snippet: Sunni political leaders have blamed the militias for the death of the tribal leader Sheikh Qasim Sweidan al-Janabi, who was abducted in southern Baghdad.
abstract: Sunni lawmakers in Iraq announce week-long boycott of Parliamentary sessions, effort to force Prime Min Haider el-Abadi to rein in Shiite militias; announcement follows abduction and murder of Sunni tribal leader Sheikh Qasim Sweidan al-Janabi, which Sunnis have blamed on militias.

byline.contributor: Omar Al-Jawoshy and Falih Hassan contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Sunni political leaders have blamed the militias for the death of the tribal leader Sheikh Qasim Sweidan al-Janabi, who was abducted in southern Baghdad.

headline.main: Sunni Lawmakers to Boycott Iraqi Parliament Over Shiite Militias
headline.print_headline: Sunni Lawmakers to Boycott Iraqi Parliament Over Shiite Militias
